{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0`. Preserved work is available on the branch:\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6581-fails-java-run-org.seleniumhq.selenium-selenium-ie-driver-4.4.0-859f18a3\n\nThe most likely failing stage is the JVM test lane (`:test` / `:tckTest`). The initial failure in `logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-08T22-16-45-081511Z.log` shows 3 assertions failing because IE-specific values expected by the old test are `null` in Selenium 4.4.0 (`browserAttachTimeout`, `initialBrowserUrl`, `ignoreZoomSetting`). Automation narrowed that down, but the last candidate still fails in `logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-08T22-19-10-405739Z.log`: `settingIeOptionsCapabilityAcceptsMapsAndCapabilities()` expects `org.openqa.selenium.Capabilities`, but Selenium is returning `java.util.ImmutableCollections.MapN` for `se:ieOptions`. Metrics also ended in failure after 4 iterations, and dynamic-access coverage was unavailable for this run.\n\nPlease inspect these logs first:\n- `logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-08T22-16-45-081511Z.log`\n- `logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-08T22-18-18-461595Z.log`\n- `logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-08T22-19-10-405739Z.log`\n- `logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-08T22-21-08-320677Z.log` (secondary issue: metadata generation could not load `libnative-image-agent.so`)\n\n1. Update the generated test on the preserved branch so Selenium 4.4.0 IE options are asserted from `se:ieOptions` using the runtime type Selenium actually returns, instead of assuming top-level capabilities or a `Capabilities` object.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-ie-driver:4.4.0` and confirm the JVM test lane passes.\n3. If the JVM tests pass, fix the local `native-image-agent` setup and re-run metadata/native verification."}}
